🌐 Subnet & Subnetting
1️⃣ What is Subnet?

        Subnet = Sub Network
        
        Matlab ek bada network ko tod kar chhote-chhote networks banana.
        
        Kyun? → Taaki IP address ka sahi use ho, aur network traffic manage ho.

        👉 Example:
        Tu ek colony ka malik hai jisme 100 ghar (devices) aa sakte hain.
        But abhi tere paas sirf 20 log rehte hain.
        Poore 100 ghar reserve karne ki zarurat nahi → tu colony ko chhote blocks (subnets) me tod dega.

2️⃣ What is Subnetting?

        Process of dividing a large network into small parts.
        
        Har subnet ka apna Network ID aur Broadcast ID hota hai.
        
        Isse devices organize hote hain aur IP waste nahi hota.

3️⃣ Why Subnetting?

        Efficient IP usage (no wastage).
        
        Better network security (ek subnet dusre se alag ho sakta hai).
        
        Easy management (ek bada crowd ko tod kar groups banana).
        
        Reduces congestion (traffic divide ho jata hai).

🔎 Types of Subnetting
✅ 1. FLSM (Fixed Length Subnet Mask)

        Har subnet same size ka hota hai.
        
        Example: Agar tere paas 100 IP hain → tu har subnet me 25-25 IP karega.
        
        Easy to calculate, but thoda IP waste hota hai.

✅ 2. VLSM (Variable Length Subnet Mask)

        Har subnet different size ka ho sakta hai (requirement ke hisaab se).
        
        Example:
        
        Subnet A → 50 users
        
        Subnet B → 20 users
        
        Subnet C → 10 users

👉 Yaha har group ko utne hi IP mile jitne usko chahiye.

Zyada efficient hai, but calculation thoda tough hai.

🎯 Subnetting Ek Line Me

        Subnet = Big network tod kar small network.
        
        FLSM = Equal size subnets.
        
        VLSM = Different size subnets (no wastage).

💡 Example for better clarity:
Suppose tu ek company me hai jisme 200 IPs available hain.

        HR dept → 100 IPs chahiye
        
        IT dept → 50 IPs chahiye
        
        Sales dept → 20 IPs chahiye

👉 Agar tu FLSM use karega to sabko equal IPs dene padenge → waste hoga.
👉 Agar tu VLSM use karega to sabko utne hi IPs milenge jitne required hai → efficient hai.
